tweet: #Chainlink daily chart and sentiment reminds me a lot of #Ethereum in the beginning of it's run from 10-15$. I was on reddit at the time and noone actually knew what was going on. There was no major news, no big event coming and people 'agreed' that it will correct soon.

Investing post. On a brief scan, I see maybe 5-6 projects above $LINK that are even arguably priced fair value. Meanwhile LINK, at $170 million, is important to a number of multibillion $ companies. It's the only project in the top 50 that I can say is clearly undervalued.
